{"title": "Silver Shadow, and Other Day Dreams", "description": "Frank Boreham was a well known preacher who served in England, Australia, and New Zealand. He published dozens of books and thousands of editorials during his lifetime, with no sign of slowing down, even up until his death at age 88. He wrote with a distinctive style, seeming to be able to draw a spiritual lesson out of any conceivable topic.<br><br>\r\n\r\nBoreham admits that this volume is but a collection of his reflections on things. But he hopes that by viewing the reflections, we will be more apt to take notice of the things themselves than if we had looked directly at them in full light of day. - Summary by Devorah Allen", "duration": 25564, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "7199", "name": "Frank W. Boreham"}], "coverArt": null, "copyright_year": "1918", "genres": ["Essays & Short Works", "Christianity - Other"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Devorah Allen"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Devorah Allen"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Larry Wilson"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "By Way of Introduction", "readers": [11084], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/silvershadow_2201_librivox/silvershadow_00_boreham_64kb.mp3", "duration": 124}, {"section": 1, "title": "Pt 1, Ch 1: Dominoes", "readers": [12980], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/silvershadow_2201_librivox/silvershadow_01_boreham_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1114}, {"section": 2, "title": "Pt 1, Ch 2: The Thrushes on the Lawn", "readers": [11084], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/silvershadow_2201_librivox/silvershadow_02_boreham_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1025}, {"section": 3, "title": "Pt 1, Ch 3: Gyp", "readers": [16576], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/silvershadow_2201_librivox/silvershadow_03_boreham_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1142}, {"section": 4, "title": "Pt 1, Ch 4: The Minister's Wife", "readers": [8425